    "created_at": "2016-04-05T17:36:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2016-04-05T17:38:26Z",
    "body": "I am not debating that XP is still widely used in the wild. But it doesn't change the fact that the Electron team would have to constantly patch Chromium for it to work. And it also doesn't change the fact that the problem isn't developers are not supporting it but people are willingly and knowingly using an unsupported operating system. They should put less work into getting them to work and finally upgrade.\n\nAs far as the Navy goes using XP was a temporary solution until they upgraded. But they also [paid heavily](http://money.cnn.com/2015/06/26/technology/microsoft-windows-xp-navy-contract/) for Microsoft to continue updates while they migrated to a newer OS which should be complete in a few months.\n"
